parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine coolant failure can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine coolant breaks down and turns to brown foamy sludge
indicating a premature failure of the 5-year/150
000-mile coolant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Multiple electrical system failures can cause a range of problems, including loss of power, faulty accessories, and increased risk of accidents or fires.
symptoms: Fuses constantly burning out
all power options failing
crackling noise from under the dash
groaning/grinding noise from under the engine compartment
wheel balance issues
left blinker malfunction
right headlamp always burning out
battery acid leaking
and poor fuel economy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure or oil leaks can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Explosion sound from under the hood
oil coming from all over the engine
and engine failure despite regular maintenance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine knock or piston slap can cause engine damage, reduced performance, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Continuous tapping sound from the engine
knock or piston slap noise from the engine
especially from the number 1 piston and cylinder area
and worsening knock that can be felt through the gear shift handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine power loss can cause loss of acceleration, reduced performance, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine loses power when accelerating
RPM goes down
and engine dies down to 50 mph when attempting to pass another vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination of the roof panel can cause bubbles to form under the paint, which can lead to water leaks, rust, and structural damage, compromising the vehicle's integrity and safety.
symptoms: Bubbles forming under the paint on the roof panel
rust spots or discoloration on the roof panel
water leaks into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the door panel from the frame can cause the door to fall off while driving, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The door panel separates from the frame
the door feels loose or unstable
the door may fall off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The window leak can cause water to enter the vehicle, leading to damage to electrical components, mold, and mildew, and compromising the vehicle's safety and comfort.
symptoms: Water leaks into the vehicle through the driver's side window
water spots or stains on the interior
musty or mildew odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake violently when braking, which can lead to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: Brake shudder or vibration when applying brakes
especially at high speeds
steering wheel shakes violently
rotors need to be turned or replaced frequently.
